The paper discusses the theoretical foundation of co-training and disagreement-based approaches for improving learning performance. These approaches are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of these approaches in computer vision (cs.CV) and data science (cs.DS), which further supports these sub-categories as likely candidates.
